word_mean_info__list.difference: 普通用词，含义广泛，侧重因某种原因所产生的最终结果，而不是眼前的结果。
指因某种原因直接产生的结果，着重持续稳定与其影响。
普通用词，多指事物经过一系列发展变化所导致的最终结局，而不是某种原因的直接结果。常可与result通用。
多指随某一事件引起的，必然或自然的不良结果，不强调直接的因果关系，而侧重事件发展的逻辑关系。

bilingual.target: 这种决定可能会带来严重的后果。

bilingual.source: The consequence of this behavior is unpredictable.
bilingual.target: 这种行为的后果是不可预见的。

bilingual.source: He did not consider the consequence of his actions.
bilingual.target: 他没有考虑到他的行为的后果。

bilingual.source: The consequence of his actions was a broken friendship.
bilingual.target: 他的行为的后果是友谊破裂。

bilingual.source: The consequence of the storm was widespread flooding.
bilingual.target: 暴风雨的后果是大范围的洪水。

bilingual.source: They ignored the consequence of environmental protection.
bilingual.target: 他们忽视了环境保护的后果。

bilingual.source: Ignoring the warning signs can have serious consequence.
bilingual.target: 忽视警告信号可能会有严重的后果。

bilingual.source: The consequence of not studying for the exam was a failing grade.
bilingual.target: 不复习考试的后果是成绩不及格。

bilingual.source: If you do not study hard, you will face bad consequence.
bilingual.target: 如果你不努力学习，你将会面对不好的后果。

bilingual.source: She didn't realize the consequence of her words until it was too late.
bilingual.target: 她没有意识到自己话语的后果，直到为时已晚。

list.abstract: Consequence（英 [ˈkɒnsɪkwəns]，美 [ˈkɑːnsɪkwens]），英语单词，作名词为结果；后果；影响。例句：Residents' hearts and lungs are affected as a consequence.（居民的心脏和肺因此受到影响。） Consequence的近义词有outcome，result，product等。
欧美男歌手，2007年发行了自己的第一张专辑《Don't Quit Your Day Job!》

yingyinNormal.en: But the melting of the Arctic has another, more serious consequence.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但北极冰盖融化会带来更严重的后果。

yingyinNormal.en: Many years ago I had a misfortune of being involved in an explosion and the consequence I get burned about 70% of my body.
yingyinNormal.zh: 多年之前，很不幸我因为一场爆炸事件导致全身约70%的皮肤烧伤。

yingyinNormal.en: Please continue with your deductions. I'm now focusing on the difference to your mental capacity a specified consequence can make.
yingyinNormal.zh: 继续推理吧。我现在关注的是，一旦明确结果对你的脑力会有何影响。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

sense_info_list.en: a result of a particular action or situation, often one that is bad or not convenient

examination_example.sentence: But it is an argument for exploring <highlight>consequences</highlight> first.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 但这是一个首先探索后果的论点。

examination_example.sentence: It is much harder, however, to understand their negative <highlight>consequences</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 然而，要理解它们的负面后果要困难得多。

examination_example.sentence: The <highlight>consequence</highlight> is that you perceive that the trip has taken less time than it actually has.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 结果是，你感觉这次旅行花费的时间比实际少。

word_usage.usage:
作名词指“后果”时：
consequence最常用以指可能产生的负面结果，常与harmful、negative、serious等词连用。即使没有形容词修饰，consequence也常含负面结果之意。
result常用于某事过去之后引起的结果。
outcome常用于谈及行动或过程可能会产生的结果。

disambiguation_list.sense_disambiguation: 着重具有或可能具有重要或深远的结果或效果。
为一般用语，着重本身具有重大价值、意义等意思。

数据源自2016.6-2023.6年8年间全六级试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2016-2023年51套试卷，包括阅读、听力、翻译等所有题型。

sense_info_list.en: a result of a particular action or situation, often one that is bad or not convenient

examination_example.sentence: The promises of technology will never be realised as fully as we hope; they will be limited by their unforeseen and unintended <highlight>consequences</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 对技术的期望将永远不会像我们希望的那样完全得以实现；它们将受到无法预见和非计划中的后果的限制。

examination_example.sentence: Westerners with disposable incomes have often behaved as if they have a right to go wherever they choose with little regard for the <highlight>consequences</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 拥有可支配收入的西方人经常表现得好像他们有权去他们选择的任何地方，而很少考虑后果。

examination_example.sentence: Perhaps the most dramatic example of the negative <highlight>consequences</highlight> of poor communication between scientists and the public is the issue of climate change.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 科学家与公众之间沟通不畅所带来的负面后果中，最戏剧性的例子也许是气候变化问题了。

examination_example.sentence: By taking upon the role of adviser rather than decision maker, one does not suffer the <highlight>consequences</highlight> of decision.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 通过扮演顾问而非决策者的角色，一个人不会承受做决定的后果。

examination_example.sentence: The <highlight>consequences</highlight> of technological innovation need not be exaggerated.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 不必夸大技术创新的后果。

sense_info_list.en: a result of a particular action or situation; often one that is bad or not convenient

examination_example.sentence: "It can lead to very serious health <highlight>consequences</highlight> for individuals who become isolated and disconnected."
examination_example.sentence_trans: “对于那些变得孤立和不联系他人的人来说，它可能会导致非常严重的健康后果。”

examination_example.sentence: It is necessary for the companies and state agencies involved to consider the ethical <highlight>consequences</highlight> of these potential changes to build a better future for all.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 有关公司和国家机构有必要考虑这些潜在变化的道德后果，为所有人建设一个更美好的未来。

examination_example.sentence: Residents' hearts and lungs are affected as a <highlight>consequence</highlight> All of which, combined with California's reputation as the home of technological innovation, makes the place ideal for developing and testing systems designed to monitor pollution in detail.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 居民的心肺都会因此受到影响，再加上加州素有科技创新之乡的美誉，这使得该地成为开发和测试旨在详细监测污染系统的理想场所。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2015-2022年8年间全国卷和自主命题省市高考卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2015-2022年全国卷高考试卷，包括阅读、完形、单选、填空、听力、改错、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选各省市考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2015-2022年8年间全国卷和自主命题省市高考卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

sense_info_list.en: a result of a particular action or situation, often one that is bad or not convenient

examination_example.sentence: Only if we discuss the <highlight>consequences</highlight> of our biophysical limits, can we have the hope to reduce their "speed, severity and harm".
examination_example.sentence_trans: 只有讨论生物物理极限的后果，我们才有希望降低它们的“速度、严重性和危害性”。

examination_example.sentence: Enviable as the cool kids may have seemed, Dr. Prinstein's studies show unpleasant <highlight>consequences</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 尽管这些酷孩子看起来令人羡慕，但Prinstein博士的研究却发现了令人不快的后果。
